cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses a new network structure for image processing, text, and audio that can adapt to different input sizes. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Among these, computer vision (cs.CV) is the most likely category since the paper focuses on image processing. Natural language processing (cs.CL) is also likely since the paper mentions the ability to handle text inputs. Machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE) are also possible categories since the paper proposes a new network structure. Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is less likely but still possible since the paper deals with adapting to different input sizes, which is a common problem in AI.
